- 'Average points' is the total points scored by a player divided by the number of games played;
- 'At least 10 games' ensures that the player has a significant sample size to evaluate their performance.

- "Consistently perform well" refers to scoring more than 10 points in games where their plays were successful;
- "Stay energized" refers to having a lower average fatigue level;
- The overall average points scored by all players is used as a benchmark for performance;
- "Forward" is a specific position played by the player.
